nings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 8,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Per kairos-contract.md. Add mode types to domain, service to application. Prompt precedence must be deterministic and testable.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-009\"\n      ],\n      \"completionNotes\": \"Completed by agent\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-014\",\n      \"title\": \"Mode-aware tool visibility\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want tool visibility to change based on the current assistant mode so that irrelevant tools are hidden.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Each mode defines a tool allowlist\",\n        \"ToolRegistry supports filtered view by mode via definitions_for_mode(mode) method\",\n        \"Brief mode hides high-risk tools\",\n        \"Tool allowlist output is deterministic and testable\",\n        \"Mode switch takes effect immediately without restart\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 8,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Add definitions_for_mode(mode) method to ToolRegistry. Wire into agent loop's tool list construction.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-013\"\n      ],\n      \"completionNotes\": \"Completed by agent\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-015\",\n      \"title\": \"ModeCoordinatorService implementation\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want mode coordination logic per coordinator-mode-contract.md so that env mode and session mode are reconciled deterministically.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"ModeCoordinatorService trait with: resolve_effective_mode(input: ModeResolutionInput) -> EffectiveMode\",\n        \"ModeCoordinatorService trait with: reconcile_on_resume(session_mode: Option<SessionMode>) -> ModeReconcileResult\",\n        \"Explicit precedence rule: session mode takes precedence over env mode (CLAUDE_CODE_COORDINATOR_MODE)\",\n        \"reconcile_on_resume(): handles mode conflict when resuming a session deterministically\",\n        \"Mode switch event carries stable metadata (from, to, reason)\",\n        \"CoordinatorModeError variants: DisabledByPolicy, InvalidModeTransition, SessionModeMismatch\",\n        \"Invalid transitions return InvalidModeTransition error\",\n        \"Unit tests for precedence logic\",\n        \"Unit tests for reconciliation on resume\",\n        \"Unit tests for each error variant\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 9,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Per coordinator-mode-contract.md. Implement in application crate. Env var: CLAUDE_CODE_COORDINATOR_MODE.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-013\"\n      ],\n      \"completionNotes\": \"Completed by agent\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-016\",\n      \"title\": \"TriggerSchedulerService local scheduling\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to schedule durable agent tasks that survive process restart so that I can automate recurring workflows.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"TriggerSchedulerService trait with: create(task: TriggerTask) -> Result<TriggerTask, TriggerError>\",\n        \"TriggerSchedulerService trait with: list() -> Result<Vec<TriggerTask>, TriggerError>\",\n        \"TriggerSchedulerService trait with: delete(id, actor: TriggerOwner) -> Result<(), TriggerError>\",\n        \"TriggerTask supports SessionOnly and Durable scope\",\n        \"Durable tasks persist to state-store and reload on restart\",\n        \"SessionOnly tasks survive runtime tick but not process restart\",\n        \"TriggerOwner model: MainAgent, Teammate(String), TeamLead\",\n        \"Durable tasks require explicit user intent\",\n        \"Teammate cannot create Durable tasks (returns DurableNotAllowedForTeammate)\",\n        \"Delete checks owner identity before removing (returns OwnershipViolation on mismatch)\",\n        \"TriggerError variants: GateDisabled, InvalidCron, OwnershipViolation, DurableNotAllowedForTeammate, Unauthorized, UpstreamRemoteError, StorageError\",\n        \"Unit tests for ownership rules\",\n        \"Unit tests for scope rules (SessionOnly vs Durable)\",\n        \"Unit tests for each error variant\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 10,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Per agent-triggers-contract.md. Add trigger types to domain, service to application, storage to session/cron crate.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-009\"\n      ],\n      \"completionNotes\": \"Completed by agent\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-017\",\n      \"title\": \"RemoteTriggerDispatchService\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want remote trigger dispatch so that scheduled tasks can execute on remote infrastructure.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"RemoteTriggerDispatchService trait with: dispatch(payload: serde_json::Value) -> Result<String, TriggerError>\",\n        \"Feature gate controls availability (gate off returns GateDisabled)\",\n        \"Requires auth/org context validation (missing auth returns Unauthorized)\",\n        \"Transport errors mapped to UpstreamRemoteError (do not leak internal details)\",\n        \"Local scheduling works independently when remote is disabled\",\n        \"Unit tests for gate-off path\",\n        \"Unit tests for auth validation\",\n        \"Unit tests for error non-leakage\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 11,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Per agent-triggers-contract.md. Depends on remote-runtime crate existing. Wire feature gate in config.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-016\",\n        \"US-019\"\n      ],\n      \"completionNotes\": \"Completed by agent\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-018\",\n      \"title\": \"Remote runtime crate — RemoteSessionService\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want bridge mode remote session management per bridge-mode-contract.md.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"New crates/remote-runtime added as workspace member\",\n        \"RemoteSessionService trait with: create_session(req) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, RemoteSessionError>\",\n        \"RemoteSessionService trait with: fetch_session(session_id) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, RemoteSessionError>\",\n        \"RemoteSessionService trait with: archive_session(session_id, policy) -> Result<(), RemoteSessionError>\",\n        \"RemoteSessionService trait with: update_title(session_id, title) -> Result<(), RemoteSessionError>\",\n        \"RemoteSessionService trait with: reconcile_resume(session_id) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, RemoteSessionError>\",\n        \"RemoteSessionState state machine with 7 states: Pending, Running, Idle, RequiresAction, Archived, Expired, Failed\",\n        \"Allowed transitions: Pending→Running|Idle|RequiresAction|Failed; Running→Idle|RequiresAction|Archived|Failed|Expired; Idle→Running|Archived|Expired; RequiresAction→Running|Archived|Expired\",\n        \"Terminal states: Archived, Expired, Failed (no outgoing transitions)\",\n        \"Forbidden transitions enforced: Archived→Running, Expired→Running\",\n        \"Archive is idempotent (409 treated as success-equivalent)\",\n        \"RemoteSessionError variants: DisabledByPolicy, EntitlementDenied, InvalidStateTransition, NotFound, Expired, AuthUnavailable, Upstream(String)\",\n        \"Missing token/org context is a policy error in app-services; runtime returns typed transport/auth errors only\",\n        \"Shutdown path can degrade to best-effort archive under timeout budget\",\n        \"Runtime errors translated in app-services into stable RemoteSessionError\",\n        \"Unit tests for all state transitions (allowed + forbidden)\",\n        \"Unit tests for 409 idempotent archive\",\n        \"Unit tests for each error variant\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 10,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Per bridge-mode-contract.md. Create crates/remote-runtime/. State types go in domain, service trait in ports, impl in application.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-009\"\n      ],\n      \"completionNotes\": \"Completed by agent\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-019\",\n      \"title\": \"CcrClient HTTP transport layer\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want an HTTP client for remote session API communication.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"CcrClient trait with: create(req) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, CcrClientError>\",\n        \"CcrClient trait with: get(session_id) -> Result<RemoteSessionSummary, CcrClientError>\",\n        \"CcrClient trait with: archive(session_id) -> Result<ArchiveResult, CcrClientError>\",\n        \"CcrClient trait with: patch_title(session_id, title) -> Result<(), CcrClientError>\",\n        \"Session ID prefix translation (session_ vs cse_) handled only in remote-runtime — app-services never manipulates tag prefixes directly\",\n        \"Auth token and org context auto-attached to requests\",\n        \"Timeout and retry configurable via config\",\n        \"CcrClientError variants: Http(String), Timeout, Unauthorized, Forbidden, InvalidPayload\",\n        \"CcrClientError and RemoteSessionError are separate error layers with translation in app-services\",\n        \"Prefix translation (session_ vs cse_) round-trips correctly through compatibility adapter\",\n        \"Unit tests for prefix translation round-trip\",\n        \"Unit tests for each CcrClientError variant\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 11,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Per bridge-mode-contract.md. Implement in crates/remote-runtime/src/client.rs. Use reqwest. Prefix translation is transport compatibility logic, not domain logic.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-018\"\n      ],\n      \"completionNotes\": \"Completed by agent\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-020\",\n      \"title\": \"UltraplanService state machine\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want to launch long-running planning sessions on remote infrastructure with lifecycle management.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"UltraplanService trait with: launch(prompt, policy) -> Result<UltraplanSession, UltraplanError>\",\n        \"UltraplanService trait with: poll(session_id) -> Result<UltraplanPhase, UltraplanError>\",\n        \"UltraplanService trait with: stop(session_id) -> Result<(), UltraplanError>\",\n        \"UltraplanService trait with: archive_orphan(session_id) -> Result<(), UltraplanError>\",\n        \"8-state machine (UltraplanPhase): Idle, Launching, Polling, AwaitingInput, Approved, Stopping, Completed, Failed\",\n        \"Transitions: Idle→Launching; Launching→Polling|Failed; Polling→AwaitingInput|Approved|Failed|Stopping; AwaitingInput→Polling|Stopping; Approved→Completed; Stopping→Completed|Failed\",\n        \"Terminal states: Completed, Failed\",\n        \"At most one active ULTRAPLAN per session context\",\n        \"Launch while already Launching/Polling returns AlreadyActive\",\n        \"Keyword auto-route must respect launch/polling guards\",\n        \"Failure after remote session creation auto-attempts orphan archive\",\n        \"Stop clears local 