        \"Unit tests for fan-out write-scope conflict policy\",\n        \"Unit tests for synthesis logic\",\n        \"Unit tests for idempotent stop\",\n        \"Unit tests for each error variant\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 14,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Per multi-agent-orchestration-contract.md. Implement in application crate. Uses tokio::spawn for parallel workers.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-015\",\n        \"US-009\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-024\",\n      \"title\": \"AgentTool and TaskStopTool integration\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user, I want the coordinator agent to spawn and manage worker agents via tools.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"AgentTool supports spawning workers with WorkerTaskSpec\",\n        \"TaskStopTool supports stopping a running worker\",\n        \"Worker results reported as WorkerResultNotification\",\n        \"Notification routing to coordinator's handle_notification\",\n        \"Non-coordinator mode blocks orchestration calls with explicit policy error (DisabledByMode)\",\n        \"UI displays worker status (Running / Completed / Failed / Cancelled)\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 14,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Extend existing crates/tools/src/spawn_agent.rs. Add TaskStopTool. Wire notification routing in bootstrap.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-023\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-025\",\n      \"title\": \"Cross-feature integration contracts enforcement\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want cross-feature integration contracts enforced per integration-contracts.md.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Bridge x Ultraplan: remote session APIs only through app-services\",\n        \"Bridge x Ultraplan: launch failure after session creation always issues archive attempt\",\n        \"Bridge x Ultraplan: archived session cannot re-enter running state\",\n        \"Bridge x Ultraplan: concurrent operations do not corrupt active session pointer state\",\n        \"MCP x Tool Runtime: cleanup hooks run on normal completion and interruption\",\n        \"MCP x Tool Runtime: privileged capability cannot be activated via generic MCP registration\",\n        \"MCP x Tool Runtime: policy failure prevents side effects\",\n        \"TeamMem x KAIROS: secret-detected content is never emitted in prompt payload\",\n        \"TeamMem x KAIROS: invalid path keys are blocked and logged safely\",\n        \"TeamMem x KAIROS: sync conflict retries remain bounded and observable\",\n        \"Triggers x Remote: remote gate-off path keeps local tasks intact\",\n        \"Triggers x Remote: durable/session-only semantics survive restart\",\n        \"Triggers x Remote: ownership violations return deterministic policy errors\",\n        \"Coordinator x Multi-Agent: parallel fan-out occurs only when write-scope conflicts absent\",\n        \"Coordinator x Multi-Agent: mixed worker outcomes produce deterministic aggregate status\",\n        \"Coordinator x Multi-Agent: final summary contains findings and actionable next steps with task traceability\",\n        \"Unified error envelope: policy / auth / transport / state / validation categories with correlation ID\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 15,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Per integration-contracts.md. Add integration tests asserting each cross-feature boundary rule. Each of the 5 cross-feature pairs has 3 test cases.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-012\",\n        \"US-014\",\n        \"US-017\",\n        \"US-020\",\n        \"US-022\",\n        \"US-024\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-026\",\n      \"title\": \"Observability baseline\",\n      \"description\": \"As an operator, I want structured logging and trace IDs across all runtime crates.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"All async operations have tracing spans\",\n        \"Correlation ID propagates from CLI entry to provider call\",\n        \"Error logs include structured context (session_id, provider, tool_name)\",\n        \"RUST_LOG env var controls log level\",\n        \"Sensitive data (API keys, tokens) never appears in logs\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 15,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Add tracing spans to application, provider, tools, mcp-runtime, remote-runtime. Add correlation ID to AppState or pass via tracing context.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-012\",\n        \"US-019\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-027\",\n      \"title\": \"IME correctness for CJK input\",\n      \"description\": \"As a user inputting Chinese, I want correct IME handling in the REPL.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Preedit / commit separation handled correctly\",\n        \"Grapheme-aware backspace (does not delete half a character)\",\n        \"Display width cursor alignment (fullwidth chars occupy two columns)\",\n        \"Pressing Enter during IME composition does not submit incomplete text\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 15,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Per acceptance-spec.md IME requirements. May need unicode-width and unicode-segmentation crates. Test with CJK input in REPL.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-001\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-028\",\n      \"title\": \"Security audit and hardening\",\n      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want security controls verified before release.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"cargo audit reports no known vulnerabilities\",\n        \"Secret scanning covers all TEAMMEM and config paths\",\n        \"Tool sandbox permissions default to deny (fail-closed)\",\n        \"Remote endpoints do not leak internal error details\",\n        \"All feature gates default to off\",\n        \"cargo fmt --check passes\",\n        \"cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings passes\",\n        \"cargo test --workspace passes\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 16,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"Per acceptance-spec.md security requirements. Run cargo audit, verify deny-by-default in sandbox config, check error messages in remote-runtime.\",\n      \"dependsOn\": [\n        \"US-025\",\n        \"US-026\",\n        \"US-027\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-029\",\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_24","type":"agent_message","text":"I now have enough context to proceed with implementation. I’m drafting a focused plan and then will execute it with test-first cycles so we can satisfy every acceptance criterion and still keep the code aligned with existing application patterns.\n\nPlan:\n1. Add a concrete `DefaultUltraplanService` in `crates/application` with:\n- phase transition validator for the 8-state graph\n- local active-session marker and guard (`AlreadyActive` for launch/polling)\n- launch/poll/stop/archive methods implementing required policy and cleanup behavior\n- keyword auto-route guard helper that blocks relaunch during launch/polling\n2. Write failing unit tests first for:\n- allowed transitions and terminal-state behavior\n- guard conditions (`AlreadyActive`, concurrent launch)\n- failure-after-creation archive attempt\n- stop clearing local active marker before returning\n- each `UltraplanError` variant\n3. Export the new module in `lib.rs` and wire tests module.\n4. Run `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings`, and `cargo test --workspace`.\n5. Commit with `feat: US-020 - UltraplanService state machine`."}}
